Hi,

I am using dynamic pages populated by a custom object.
The list of crm objects is displayed using the hubl <https://developers.HubSpot.com/docs/cms/hubl/functions#:~:text=than%20range%3D).-,crm_objects,-Gets%20a%20list|crm_objects> function.
I am filtering the dynamic list by adding query parameters to the url, which then updates the crm_objects query param.

All of the above is working fine.

I now want to do something similar but using a search bar. The search input will be used to find a given text property that partially contains the value.

I see in the docs that it mentions ‘startwith’ but I can’t get it to work. Do you know how ‘startwith’ should be called? I already tried this and a few other variations: "event_name__startswith=Dublin 2020"
Do you have some more context? Are you willing to achieve this through a custom module in CMS Hub?
Where are you fetching the data from?

Hi! I'm trying to create a competitor's landing page template that can adjust its content, especially the table. It requires a table that needs to be updated per competitor. The data will come from the content editor in charge of populating the LPs.
